{{Infobox tennis event|2010|Chang-Sat Bangkok 2 Open| | date=20 – 26 September | edition=1st | location=[[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]] | champs={{flagicon|BUL}} [[Grigor Dimitrov]] | champd={{flagicon|THA}} [[Sanchai Ratiwatana]] / {{flagicon|THA}} [[Sonchat Ratiwatana]] }}
The '''2010 [[Chang-Sat Bangkok 2 Open]]''' was a professional [[tennis]] tournament played on [[hard court]]s. It was the first edition of the tournament which was part of the [[2010 ATP Challenger Tour]]. It took place in [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]] between 20 and 26 September 2010.
==ATP entrants== ===Seeds=== {| class="wikitable" border="1" |- ! Nationality ! Player ! Ranking* ! Seeding |- | {{flag|BRA}} | [[Ricardo Mello]] | 75 | 1 |- | {{flag|BEL}} | <s>[[Olivier Rochus]]</s> | <s>79</s> | <s>2</s> |- | {{flag|USA}} | [[Michael Russell (tennis)|Michael Russell]] | 84 | 3 |- | {{flag|JPN}} | [[Go Soeda]] | 110 | 4 |- | {{flag|BEL}} | <s>[[Steve Darcis]]</s> | <s>117</s> | <s>5</s> |- | {{flag|AUS}} | <s>[[Peter Luczak]]</s> | <s>126</s> | <s>6</s> |- | {{flag|CRO}} | [[Ivan Dodig]] | 133 | 7 |- | {{flag|GER}} | [[Denis Gremelmayr]] | 140 | 8 |}
* Rankings are as of September 13, 2010.
===Other entrants=== The following players received wildcards into the singles main draw: * {{flagicon|THA}} [[Weerapat Doakmaiklee]] * {{flagicon|THA}} [[Peerakiat Siriluethaiwattana]] * {{flagicon|THA}} [[Danai Udomchoke]] * {{flagicon|THA}} [[Kittipong Wachiramanowong]]
The following players received entry from the qualifying draw: * {{flagicon|USA}} [[Ryler DeHeart]] * {{flagicon|GER}} [[Peter Gojowczyk]] * {{flagicon|DEN}} [[Frederik Nielsen]] * {{flagicon|GBR}} [[James Ward (tennis)|James Ward]]
The following players received a [[lucky loser]] spot: * {{flagicon|IND}} [[Yuki Bhambri]] * {{flagicon|USA}} [[Alex Bogomolov Jr.]] * {{flagicon|CHN}} [[Gong Maoxin]] * {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Nick Lindahl]] * {{flagicon|GER}} [[Sebastian Rieschick]] * {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Yang Tsung-hua]]
