The '''Federação Norte-rio-grandense de Futebol''' ([[English language|English]]: Football Association of Rio Grande do Norte state) was founded on July 14, 1918, and it manages all the official [[association football|football]] tournaments within the state of [[Rio Grande do Norte]], which are the [[Campeonato Potiguar]], the [[Campeonato Potiguar (lower levels)|Campeonato Potiguar lower levels]] and the [[Copa RN]], and represents the clubs at the [[Brazilian Football Confederation|Brazilian Football Confederation (CBF)]].

