{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Longton Cricket Club Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Stoke-on-Trent]], [[Staffordshire]] | establishment = 1954 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year4 = 1976 | club4 = [[Minor Counties East]] | year3 = 1975 | club3 = [[Minor Counties North]] | year2 = 1959-1960, 1969 & 1972 | club2 = [[Minor Counties cricket team|Minor Counties]] | year1 = 1954-present | club1 = [[Staffordshire County Cricket Club|Staffordshire]] | date = 14 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/759.html Ground profile }}
'''Longton Cricket Club Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Stoke-on-Trent]], [[Staffordshire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1954, when [[Staffordshire County Cricket Club|Staffordshire]] played [[Northumberland County Cricket Club|Northumberland]] in the grounds first [[Minor Counties Championship]] match. From 1954 to present, the ground has hosted 40 Minor Counties Championship matches<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/759_minc.html Minor Counties Championship Matches played on Longton Cricket Club Ground]</ref> and 7 [[MCCA Knockout Trophy]] matches.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/759_mint.html MCCA Knockout Trophy Matches played on Longton Cricket Club Ground]</ref>
A combined [[Minor Counties cricket team|Minor Counties]] team has used the ground for 4 [[first-class cricket|first-class]] matches, the first of which came in 1955 against the touring [[ISiuth Africa national cricket team|South Africans]]. The last first-class match held on the ground came in 1972 and saw the Minor Counties play the touring [[Australia national cricket team|Australians]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/759_f.html First-Class Matches played on Longton Cricket Club Ground]</ref>
The ground has held [[List-A cricket|List-A]] matches. Staffordshire have played two List-A matches at the ground against [[Glamorgan County Cricket Club|Glamorgan]] in the [[1971 Gillette Cup]] and [[Leicestershire County Cricket Club|Leicestershire]] in the [[1975 Gillette Cup]]. [[Minor Counties North]] played a single List-A match at the ground in the 1975 [[Benson and Hedges Cup]] against [[Lancashire County Cricket Club|Lancashire]]. [[Minor Counties East]] used the ground for a single List-A match against [[Northamptonshire County Cricket Club|Northamptonshire]] in the 1976 Benson and Hedges Cup.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/759_a.html List-A Matches played on Longton Cricket Club Ground]</ref>
In local domestic cricket, Longton Cricket Club Ground is the home ground of [[Longton Cricket Club]] who play in the [[North Staffordshire and South Cheshire League]].<ref>[http://longton.play-cricket.com/home/home.asp Longton Cricket Club] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120717060457/http://longton.play-cricket.com/home/home.asp |date=2012-07-17 }}</ref>
